## **1️⃣ Airbnb Data Analysis**  

### 📍 Problem Statement  
Airbnb hosts struggle with **pricing strategies** and **seasonal demand fluctuations**. This project analyzes historical data to optimize **occupancy rates, pricing, and revenue**.  

### 📊 Data Source  
- **Source:** [Inside Airbnb](http://insideairbnb.com/get-the-data.html)  
- **Datasets Used:** Listings, Reviews, Calendar (Cleaned & Processed).  

### 🛠 Tools Used  
- **Python** (Pandas, Seaborn, Matplotlib, FPDF)  
- **SQL** (PostgreSQL for data aggregation)  
- **Tableau** (Visual dashboards)  

### 🔍 Key Findings  
✔ **Peak Booking Seasons:** Demand is highest from **June - August** (summer months).  
✔ **Superhost Impact:** Superhosts charge **20-30% higher rates** and still get more bookings.  
✔ **Top Neighborhoods:** [List of profitable areas] based on occupancy and price.  

### 📊 Visualizations  
📌 Seasonal trends: ![Occupancy Trends](visualizations/seasonal_trends.png)  
📌 Revenue by neighborhood: ![Revenue Analysis](visualizations/revenue_by_neighborhood.png)  

### 📑 Business Recommendations  
✅ **Dynamic Pricing:** Adjust prices based on seasonal trends.  
✅ **Invest in Superhost Status:** Higher trust = More bookings.  
✅ **Location Strategy:** Focus on high-revenue neighborhoods.  

